cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper presents a distributed-memory parallel algorithm for triangle counting. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper deals with a fundamental graph analytic operation. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as triangle counting is extensively used in network science. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses communication overheads and optimizations related to the sparsity of the graph. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper presents experiments on synthetic and real-world graphs to evaluate the performance of the proposed algorithm.
